children.name: Mn
children.label: Manufacturer
children.description: Well known value registered with SunSpec for compliance

children.name: Rte
children.label: Rate
children.description: Interface baud rate in bits per second

children.name: Bits
children.label: Bits
children.description: Number of data bits per character

children.name: CmdBits
children.label: Control Bits
children.notes: Message required at a rate of at least once per second in all states.

children.name: CmdRealPwr
children.label: Real Power Command
children.description: Commanded real power (W) while in grid following mode - positive real power is defined as power being put into the ac network.

children.name: CmdReactivePwr
children.label: Reactive Power Command
children.description: Commanded reactive power (VA) while in grid following mode - positive reactive power is defined as the converter having a leading power factor.

children.name: CmdV
children.label: Voltage Command
children.description: Desired output voltage while in grid forming mode.

children.name: CmdHz
children.label: Frequency Command
children.description: Desired output frequency while in grid forming mode.

children.name: CtlSrc
children.label: Control Source
children.description: Master control source for the inverter

children.name: IMPPT
children.label: MPPT Current
children.description: Measured MPPT current (Hydra Solar inverter only)

children.name: Vsol
children.label: Solar Voltage
children.description: Measured solar input voltage (Hydra Solar inverter only)

children.name: Vbat
children.label: Battery Voltage
children.description: Measured battery input voltage (Hydra inverter only)

children.name: SysFlt
children.label: System Fault Code
children.description: Fault code (if non-0, indicates that 1 or more system faults is active)

children.name: CmdRealCurrent
children.label: Real Current Command
children.description: Commanded real current (A) while in grid following mode - positive real power is defined as power being put into the ac network.

children.name: CmdReactiveCurrent
children.label: Reactive Current Command
children.description: Commanded reactive current (A) while in grid following mode - positive reactive power is defined as the converter having a leading power factor.
